real_commentary: KICKOFF:  And we're off! France get us started.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The first half begins. Euro 2024 Semi-Final between Spain and France!

real_commentary: Bright start from Spain... Fabian Ruiz moves into the left channel and curls a cross towards the back post, but Lamine Yamal slips and the ball bounces out of play.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating early with 76.7% possession, controlling the midfield.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Yamal and Ruiz are involved again for Spain, with the former this time setting up the latter from right to left. However, Ruiz can only head his effort at the far post over the crossbar.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Lamine Yamal (Spain) on Theo Hernández (France). Free kick awarded.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Yamal and Ruiz are involved again for Spain, with the former this time setting up the latter from right to left. However, Ruiz can only head his effort at the far post over the crossbar.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Lamine Yamal (Spain) on Theo Hernández (France). Free kick awarded.

real_commentary: Kylian Mbappe - without his mask tonight after breaking his nose at the start of the tournament - had the ball poked away from his feet on the edge of the penalty area by Jesus Navas.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating early with 88.7% possession, Tchouaméni heavily involved.

real_commentary: GOAL!  SPAIN 0-1 FRANCE (KOLO MUANI)
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 0, France 0. Randal Kolo Muani heads in from close range, assisted by Kylian Mbappé.

real_commentary: GOAL!  France finally score their first goal of Euro 2024 from open play!
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 87%, controlling the midfield for 2 minutes.

real_commentary: Spain have responded well to going a goal behind as they pile bodies forward and look threatening on both wings with Yamal and Nico Williams.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Jesús Navas (Spain) shown a yellow card for a foul on Adrien Rabiot (France).

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Navas is booked for a late sliding challenge on Rabiot around 35 yards away from Spain's goal... resulting free kick for France comes to nothing, though.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Adrien Rabiot (France) is down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: France are beginning to find their rhythm... this is the best they have played at Euro 2024, although they have yet to test the gloves of Unai Simon.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 80.9%, controlling midfield play effectively.

real_commentary: GOAL!  SPAIN 1-1 FRANCE (YAMAL)
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 1, France 0. Lamine Yamal strikes with a left foot shot from the edge of the box.

real_commentary: GOAL!  Wow... that was special!
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Nico Williams. Conceded by Theo Hernández. Spain pressing hard.

real_commentary: GOAL!  SPAIN 2-1 FRANCE (OLMO)
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 2, France 0. Daniel Olmo Carvajal scores with a right footed shot from the centre of the box.

real_commentary: GOAL!
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating midfield with 84.6% possession, controlling play for 2 minutes. Ousmane Dembélé active with 6 events.

real_commentary: UEFA state, at the moment, that Spain's second goal is in fact an own goal scored by France defender Jules Kounde, but that will surely change as Olmo's strike looked on target.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating play with 91.5% possession, controlling midfield for 2 minutes. Fabián Ruiz Peña most active with 12 events.

real_commentary: Theo Hernandez leaves his mark on Yamal with a late challenge right on the touchline. Referee Slavko Vincic gives the foul but opts to keeps his cards in his pocket for this one
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Theo Hernández (France) on Lamine Yamal (Spain) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Thirty-seven brilliant minutes played in Munich so far; France have impressed despite letting a one-goal lead slip, but Spain's two goals scored just four minutes and nine seconds apart is what is separating the two teams at present.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Nico Williams, conceded by Mike Maignan. Spain pressing hard.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  France win a corner and play it short; Theo Hernandez's cross is initially kept in by William Saliba, but it fails to reach a teammate.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for France, delivered by Ousmane Dembélé, conceded by Marc Cucurella.

real_commentary: Maignan leaps well to catch the resulting corner from Williams; the France goalkeeper then tries to get his team up the pitch with an early throw, but the options were not there in front of him for a quick breakaway.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Nico Williams. Conceded by Mike Maignan.

real_commentary: As expected, UEFA have now awarded the second Spain goal to Dani Olmo, meaning the RB Leipzig attacker is officially joint top scorer at Euro 2024 with three goals.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Sergio Busquets (Spain) on Ousmane Dembélé (France) near the box.

real_commentary: Two minutes of added time.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Sergio Busquets (Spain) on Adrien Rabiot (France). Free kick awarded near the box.

real_commentary: KICKOFF:  Spain get us underway for the second half!
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The second half is underway in the Semi-Final. Spain leads France 2-0.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Maignan does well to come off his line and rush out of his box to win the ball from Williams on Spain's left flank.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by William Saliba (France) on Jesús Navas González (Spain) in midfield.

real_commentary: Ousmane Dembele does brilliantly to control a cross and stands up Spain left-back Marc Cucurella, but the PSG winger could only curl his delivery from the right into the gloves of Unai Simon... frustrating from France's perspective.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France slightly ahead in possession, but midfield remains evenly contested. Laporte active for Spain.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Mbappe cuts inside from the left and fizzes a low shot towards the near post, but Unai Simon comfortably gets behind it.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France asserting dominance with 92.9% possession, controlling the midfield for the fourth consecutive minute.

real_commentary: Spain are forced to make their first substitution of the night, as right-back Navas seems to have picked up a knock and is replaced by Athletic Bilbao centre-back Dani Vivian, meaning Nacho is set to move over to the right side of the back four.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Aurélien Tchouaméni's header from the centre of the box denied by Unai Simón.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Mbappe races down the right, easily beating Rodri for pace, before smacking a cross into the six-yard box, but Simon blocks the cross with a strong left hand.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Kylian Mbappé's right-footed shot from the right side of the box denied by Unai Simón.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Tchouameni is booked for a late lunging tackle on Morata in the middle of the pitch, preventing a Spanish counter-attack.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Adrien Rabiot (France) on Aymeric Laporte (Spain) in midfield.

real_commentary: With half an hour remaining, Deschamps has opted to roll the dice...
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Triple change for France. N'Golo Kanté, Adrien Rabiot, and Randal Kolo Muani off; Antoine Griezmann on.

real_commentary: With half an hour remaining, Deschamps has opted to roll the dice...
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Triple substitution for France. Eduardo Camavinga, Marcus Thuram, and Kingsley Coman replace Rabiot, Kolo Muani, and Kanté.

real_commentary: With half an hour remaining, Deschamps has opted to roll the dice...
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Triple substitution for France. Randal Kolo Muani, N'Golo Kanté, and Adrien Rabiot off; Bradley Barcola on.

real_commentary: Antoine Griezmann (36) has now become France's most-capped player at major tournaments, surpassing goalkeeper Hugo Lloris (35).
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 67.3%, controlling midfield play effectively.

real_commentary: France win another corner, but Dayot Upamecano heads wide at the back post... a lot of France's best chances have come through headers and this is another one that goes begging.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain has been in complete control for the last three minutes, dominating the defensive third.

real_commentary: France win another corner, but Dayot Upamecano heads wide at the back post... a lot of France's best chances have come through headers and this is another one that goes begging.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain has been in complete control for the last three minutes, dominating the defensive third.

real_commentary: Spain are yet to register a single shot on goal in the second half, while France have had three chances.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Ousmane Dembélé (France) on Álvaro Morata (Spain) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Spain have lost the spark they had in the first 45 and seem to be holding on here, as France enjoy an extended spell of possession and pose a threat in the final third.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Dayotchanculle Upamecano (France) on Álvaro Morata (Spain) in midfield.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Spain fail to clear their lines and a deflected cross from Dembele falls nicely to Theo Hernandez, in space on the edge of the box, but the French left-back blazes a right-foot shot over the crossbar.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating midfield with 100% possession, led by Daniel Olmo Carvajal's activity.

real_commentary: Spain decide to make two changes ahead of the final 10 minutes of normal time, with Olmo and Morata brought off as Mikel Merino and Mikel Oyarzabal enter the pitch.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for Spain. Mikel Merino replaces Daniel Olmo in a tactical switch.

real_commentary: Another change for France as their all-time record goalscorer Olivier Giroud is brought on for Dembele.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for France, delivered by Antoine Griezmann. Conceded by José Ignacio Fernández Iglesias.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Yamal, like the rest of his Spain teammates, has rarely threatened in the second half, but he almost put the game to bed with another speculative strike.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France maintains 58% possession, mostly in their defensive third, with Upamecano active.

real_commentary: Spain defender Aymeric Laporte is down and receiving treatment after running into the shoulder of Giroud.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Kylian Mbappé's right-footed shot from the centre of the box goes off target.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  Just moments after Laporte was cleared to continue, Mbappe was presented with a brilliant chance to restore parity fro France.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Álvaro Morata (Spain) on Mike Maignan (France) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  France are clearly getting frustrated now and Camavinga is deservedly booked for a late tackle on Marc Cucurella.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Free kick awarded to Spain after a foul by Lucas Hernandez on Fabián Ruiz Peña.
